            "favourites_count": 1,
            "edited_at": null,
            "content": "<p><span class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"><a href=\"https://mastodon.social/@evanwolf\" class=\"u-url mention\">@<span>evanwolf</span></a></span> <a href=\"https://mastodon.social/tags/climate\" class=\"mention hashtag\" rel=\"tag\">#<span>climate</span></a> /1</p><p>The Pacific circulations are weakening and changing the Pacific in dramatic ways as the outflow of cold fresh water from polar melt decreases caused by the lessened formation of ice at the pole. </p><p>However, the circulation doesn&#39;t have the same dynamics as the Atlantic circulation. </p><p>The cold water from ice melt in the Atlantic has to overcome an ocean bottom ridge. </p><p>That creates the equivalent of a switch. The AMOC can just stop. The Pacific oscillation slows.</p>",
