            "reblogs_count": 2,
            "favourites_count": 1,
            "edited_at": null,
            "content": "<p><span class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"><a href=\"https://mastodon.social/@evanwolf\" class=\"u-url mention\">@<span>evanwolf</span></a></span> <a href=\"https://mastodon.social/tags/climate\" class=\"mention hashtag\" rel=\"tag\">#<span>climate</span></a> /2</p><p>The Pacific oscillation changed dramatically 30 years ago in the 90s.</p><p>Before then when El Nino and La Nina came and went, there was a pattern.</p><p>Warm equator -&gt; cold tropics.<br />Cold equator -&gt; warm tropics.</p><p>Since the 90s, the southern tropics remains with that pattern. The northern tropic has a new pattern.</p><p>Warm equator -&gt; WARM tropic<br />Cold equator -&gt; warm tropic</p><p>I joked about that being El La Nineo. </p><p>The climate researchers didn&#39;t laugh. They also couldn&#39;t explain it.</p>",
